				<h1 class="">Home of the Eagles</h1>
<p class="">Welcome to Hondo Valley Public Schools, home of the Eagles! Located just off highways 70 and 380 in New Mexico, our small district serves students and families in the Lincoln County area. </p>
<p class="">Please take some time to get to know <a href="/Our_Schools" target="_self">our school</a> and <a href="/Administration_Staff" target="_self">staff</a>. We offer a variety of <a href="/Student_Activities_Athletics" target="_self">clubs and athletics</a> programs and take pride in preparing our students for successful life after high school. Please <a href="/Contact_Us" target="_self">contact us</a> if you have any questions.</p>
<h2 class="">A Message from Our Superintendent</h2>
<p class="">Welcome to Hondo Valley Public Schools! </p>
<p class="">As partners in education, we share the responsibility for our children’s success, and we ask that you help guide and support your child’s learning by ensuring he/she:</p>
<p class=""></p>
<ul class="">
<li class="">Attends school daily and arrives on time</li>
<li class="">Completes all homework assignments</li>
<li class="">Reads every day</li>
<li class="">Shares experiences and asks for help when needed</li>
<li class="">Knows that you expect him/her to succeed</li>
</ul>
<div class="pom-container">
<p class="">We promise to do our part to guide your children towards academic mastery and responsible citizenship and to communicate with you in a timely, effective manner so that our partnership (and our children) succeed!</p>
<p class="">Sincerely,</p>
<div class="signature">Marvin L. Martin</div>
<div class="pom-container"><p class="">Marvin L. Martin <br><span style="line-height: 1.375em;">Superintendent </span></p></div>
